A very economical Cantonese lunch--large portions of rice and three sides you pick at the hot bar in the back and a large soup for under $5 a head. More options during dinner hours too.

Good food. Very consistent and the prices are cheap for what you get. This place has been around for a long time. Plenty of seating. There's a quick sit down area or a dinning room area as well. Definitely give this place a try if you want good Cantonese style Chinese food.

This has become a staple for us due to how close it is for my grandparents to arrive here. While the service is brisk, sometimes not very helpful, I’ve come to accept that as a part of the Chinatown experience. I think besides the service and the dingy appearance of the restaurant, the food is actually pretty decent. Most things are stir fried well, the ingredients fresh enough considering the low price. Things can be salty and too oily, but you can also tell them to use little and most of the time, the kitchen will follow through with that request. I like coming here and I especially love their fish fillet with string peas and eggs stir fry. The chicken also tends to be moist and tender. Sometimes the vegetables are not as fresh and a little stringy, but when they are in season and freshly acquired, it’s nice.

Really more like 3.5 stars but the food makes up for the half star. Service is so-so, sometimes hard to get their attention. But the food is consistently good, traditional Cantonese family style food, for a really decent price. You can also get as much white rice as you want when you dine in. English menu is available at request but don't expect too much more English understanding. This place gets packed at usual meal times so even if you order takeout, be prepared to wait. Food is worth it though. My family frequents here a lot.

The cantonese style cooking here is amazing and of great value.  They offer 3 dishes for $30 which is family style combination with free traditional pork bone soup and white rice - I recommend the combination of House Special Chicken with Garlic shallots, Pork Chop with Peking Sauce,.as for the last dish try something you may like (such as Sautéed Flounder, Jumbo Shrimp with Walnuts, House Special Seafood delight, or round out with a vegetable dish).  If you need more than 3 dishes, each additonal is $10 more.  During busy times, service becomes a little inconsistent and that is where I subtract a star.

Food and services are great. Love their pork chops. Staffs are friendly. Very affordable dishes. They also offer combos. Great price.  My family and I been coming here very often for years. Their dishes are very good, simple and of great value. Their cooking bring delicious traditional Cantonese dishes to the table. It is a true Cantonese style restaurant. We usually order the common dishes such as garlic fried chicken, Peking style pork chop, eggplant garlic with chicken and salted fish, mayo shrimp with walnut and broccoli, steamed or fried fish, assorted mushroom supreme, roasted pork, filet fish with tofu, lobster or seafood e-fun noodle, black bean clam, salt and pepper squid, house traditional chicken, fried rice, veggies and so many more. Most of their dishes are really good and we never had any complains. So you can order anything and it should be good. My family don't like too oily, too spicy, too salty, too sweet or too bland food or bad services and it is hard to find somewhere that qualify these categories. Fortunately we found City Cafe.  They have combo deals at a good price which include rice and traditional broth soup. We usually order 8-15 dishes and food portions are huge, but it is not surprising that we can finish them all because they are delicious. Service has been very good for us unlike other reviews, the waiter always give us time to look at the menu and patiently answering our question. The manager takes the extra incentive to help the waiters if needed. He is always walking around to make sure everything is good, very friendly, attentive and funny. Thumps up to the manager.  City cafe might not a five star restaurant and their dishes might not be extraordinary, but they cooking brings our family comfortably together without worrying about a bad meal at the end. It is our favorite family restaurant.

They have traditional cantonese roast pork, roast pig, duck, chicken. Always busy at night. Good for big and small groups. Fishes are good porportions. Tasty dishes and never disappoints me.
